title: @OspreyVB Hosts FGCU, Stetson to Finish First Half of #ASunVB Play
text: Tickets JACKSONVILLE, Fla. â€“ The first part of Atlantic Sun play concludes for University of North Florida volleyball with two home matches at UNF Arena. The Ospreys host FGCU on Friday at 7 p.m., and then Stetson on Saturday at 5 p.m. "We are looking forward to hosting two teams that are playing extremely well right now," said head coach . "We know it is going to be a tough weekend, but after a good week of practice, we are excited to get back on the court and compete." Not only does the weekend finish up the first half of conference play, but it also concludes a four-match homestand for the Ospreys. UNF went 1-1 last weekend, suffering a 3-0 loss to Atlantic Sun leader Lipscomb, but rebounding for a 3-0 sweep of NJIT. UNF enters the weekend with a 3-2 mark in conference play and tied for third in the A-Sun standings. Friday night's match is Student Appreciation Night with the first 100 UNF students getting a voucher for a free hot dog or free popcorn. With Saturday evening's match, fans can use their tickets from the volleyball match for admission into the UNF-Stetson men's soccer game that is later that night at 7 p.m. Additionally, it will be 2-for-1 beer at Saturday's match for those that are aged 21+. Tickets are $5 for adult; $3 for Youth under 17, Senior Citizens 55+, Military and UNF Faculty and Staff with proper ID. Students with a valid Osprey1 Card and Children 2-and-under are free. Tickets can be purchased online at www.UNFOspreys.com , by phone at (904) 620-BIRD (2473) or at UNF Arena. Match Day Need to Know Dates
